feat: root shell write path; field-write fallback for stripped ListPreference setters; flatten OneSpace layout

- PrefRef.setEntries / setEntryValues / setValue: write the backing
  CharSequence[] / String fields directly when the public setter methods
  are stripped from the host APK. R8 in minify mode removes
  ListPreference.setEntries / setEntryValues entirely (logcat shows 'no
  signature-compatible method') because the host only ever populates list
  preferences from XML. The backing fields stay because the dialog
  fragment reads them; we identify them by type — the first instance
  CharSequence[] field is mEntries, the second is mEntryValues.

- RootShellFallback (Path D): when DIRECT_API, SYSTEM_BRIDGE, and
  SETTINGS_GLOBAL all fail, exec 'su' and run 'cmd settings put global
  bluetooth_select_a2dp_*' followed by a bluetooth_manager disable / sleep
  / enable so the A2DP stack renegotiates the codec on reconnect. Probes
  for su lazily and caches the answer. The user explicitly authorises
  xyz.melodylsp.codec in their root manager so this is opt-in.

- CodecBlockBuilder.buildAndInsert(..., wrapInCategory): when false, lay
  the quality / sampleRate / remember items as siblings of the existing
  top-level Preferences instead of wrapping them in a PreferenceCategory.
  OneSpace uses the flat layout to avoid the extra inter-card padding the
  bottom-sheet renderer applies around every Category (the user reported
  '间距太大了' between '通用设置' and the codec block); DetailMain keeps
  the wrapped layout because its surrounding screen depends on Category
  cards for visual grouping.

- BANNER_VIA_ROOT toast distinguishes root-write from settings-global so
  the user knows which path landed.
